<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606742>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Eupolyphaga fusca Chopard from Yunnan: A–B. Male, from Mt. Jizushan, Binchuan; C–D. Female, from Kunming; E–G. Polyphaga fusca Chopard, male, holotype (with labels), from Kunming. E–G photographed by Zong-Qing Wang, copyright The Natural History Museum, United Kingdom (NHM). Scale bar 1 cm for A–B, E–F; C–D without scale bar." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606742/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606746>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Habitus of Eupolyphaga species: A–B. Eupolyphaga robusta sp. nov., male, holotype, from Wenchuan, Sichuan; C–D. Eupolyphaga sp. 2, female, from Nang County, Tibet; E–J. Eupolyphaga sp. 1, from south Gansu: E–F, I–J. Male: E–F. Overall habitus, I. Pronotum, J. Vertex; G–H. Female, E–J photographed by Gunvi Lindberg, copyright Swedish Museum of Natural History, Sweden (NRM). K–L. Eupolyphaga sp. 4, female, from Binchuan, Yunnan. Scale bar 1 cm for A–H, K–L; I–J not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606746/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606734>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Eupolyphaga species from Tibet, China: A–C. Polyphaga thibetana Chopard, male, holotype (with labels), from Gyantse, Shigatse. D–I. Polyphaga everestiana Chopard: D–F. Male, syntype (with labels), from Mt. Everest; G–I. Female, syntype (with labels), from Mt. Everest. A–F photographed by Zong-Qing Wang, G–I provided by George Beccaloni, copyright The Natural History Museum, United Kingdom (NHM). J–M. Eupolyphaga everestiana reni subsp. nov., from Lhünzê, Lhoka: J–K. Male, holotype; L–M. Female, paratype. Scale bar 1 cm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606734/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606730>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus of Eupolyphaga species: A–B. Eupolyphaga hupingensis sp. nov., male, holotype, from Shimen, Hunan. C–D. Eupolyphaga shennongensis sp. nov., male, holotype, from Shengnongjia, Hubei. E–J. Eupolyphaga hanae sp. nov.: E–F. Male, holotype, from Dujiangyan, Sichuan; G. Male, paratype, from Mt. Simianshan, Chongqing; H. Male, paratype, from Suining, Sichuan; I–J. Female, paratype, from Dujiangyan, Sichuan. Scale bar 1 cm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606730/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606738>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Eupolyphaga species from Sichuan and Yunnan: A–B. Eupolyphaga dongi sp. nov., male, holotype, from Baoshan, Yunnan. C–E. Eupolyphaga hengduana Woo & Feng, male, holotype (with labels), from Lijiang, Yunnan. F–G. Eupolyphaga xuorum sp. nov., male, from Ya’an, Sichuan. H–J. Eupolyphaga densiguttata Feng & Woo, male, neotype (with labels), from Binchuan, Yunnan. Scale bar 1 cm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606738/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606740>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Eupolyphaga species from Yunnan, China: A–B. Eupolyphaga maculata sp. nov., male, holotype, from Mt. Cangshan, Dali. C–D. Eupolyphaga nigrifera sp. nov., male, holotype, from Fumin, Kunming. E–F. Eupolyphaga fengi sp. nov., male, paratype, from Mt. Zixishan, Chuxiong. G–H. Eupolyphaga fengi yongshengensis subsp. nov., male, holotype, from Lijiang. I–P. Eupolyphaga wooi sp. nov.: I–J. Male, holotype, from Mt. Ailaoshan, Yunnan; K–L. Male, paratype, from Changning, Yunnan; M–P. Females, paratypes, from Mt. Ailaoshan, Yunnan. Scale bar 1cm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606740/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606732>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Habitus of Eupolyphaga species: A–I. Eupolyphaga thibetana (Chopard): A–B. Male, from Shigatse, Tibet; C–D. Female, from Shigatse, Tibet; E. Female, from Dinggyê, Tibet; F–G. Male, from Dinggyê, Tibet; H–I. Male, from Chanang, Tibet. J–Q. Eupolyphaga yunnanensis (Chopard): J–K. Male, from Pantiange, Weixi, Yunnan; L–M. Male, from Kangding, Sichuan; N. Female, from Bomê, Tibet; O. Female, from Chagyab, Tibet; P–Q. Female, from Danba, Sichuan. Scale bar 1 cm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606732/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606736>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Eupolyphaga species from Yunnan, China: A–D. Eupolyphaga pilosa sp. nov., from Weixi: A–B. Male, holotype; C–D. Female, paratype. E–H. Eupolyphaga daweishana sp. nov., from Pingbian: E–F. Male, holotype; G–H. Female nymph. I–L. Eupolyphaga nigrinotum sp. nov., from Mt. Jizushan, Binchuan: I–J. Male, holotype; K–L. Female, paratype. Scale bar 1cm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606736/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2606748>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Pronotum (A, D, G), vertex (B, E, H) and face (C, F, I) features of Eupolyphaga species: A–C. Eupolyphaga densiguttata Feng & Woo; D–F. Eupolyphaga daweishana sp. nov.; G–I. Eupolyphaga wooi sp. nov. Scale bar 1 mm for all." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2606748/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

